“Gonna Be Alright” by Ryan Ellis was released on May 13th, 2022. It blends contemporary Christian pop with elements of gospel, featuring a mix of acoustic instruments and subtle electronic sounds. This combination supports the uplifting message without overwhelming it.

Chris McClarney is a contemporary Christian musician, songwriter, and worship leader known for his powerful vocals and heartfelt lyrics. He gained prominence in the Christian music scene through his involvement in leading worship at influential churches and events. "Speak to the Mountains'' was released on May 28th, 2021 as part of McClarney's EP of the same name. It emphasizes faith and resilience through the metaphor of speaking to mountains, a biblical reference that suggests the power of faith to overcome obstacles.

Every Victory" by The Belonging Co, featuring Danny Gokey, is a contemporary worship song that has made a notable impact within the Christian music community. It was released on February 5, 2021, as part of The Belonging Co's third live album "See the Light." The song has achieved commercial success, debuting at No. 40 on the US Hot Christian Songs chart and peaking at No. 29.

Jenna Davis is a multifaceted American actress, singer, voice-over artist, and social media influencer. She gained widespread recognition for her role as the voice of the titular character in the 2022 horror film M3GAN. Her music often explores themes of personal growth, relationships, and self-empowerment. "16" was released on September 25, 2020 as a single. The song is a heartfelt reflection on the experiences and emotions associated with being 16 years old. "Player" is another single by Davis, released on May 30, 2021. The song narrates the experience of dealing with someone who manipulates and plays with others' emotions.

This catalog showcases rock bands from across the globe, featuring the dynamic sounds of Japan's One Ok Rock, the American-based Sleeping With Sirens, Australia's 5 Seconds of Summer, and the UK's Lower Than Atlantis.

One Ok Rock is a Japanese rock band formed in Tokyo in 2005. The included song, "Eye of the Storm,” released in 2019, is the title track from their ninth studio album of the same name. This album marked a significant shift in the band's sound, incorporating more pop and electronic elements compared to their previous rock-oriented works. The song itself exemplifies this change, featuring a blend of electronic beats, softer melodies, and emotive lyrics that reflect themes of resilience, hope, and pushing through difficult times.

"Leave It All Behind," performed by Sleeping With Sirens served as the lead single for their sixth studio album How It Feels to Be Lost, released on June 19, 2019. The song showcased a return to the band's post-hardcore roots, featuring heavier instrumentals and more aggressive vocals and received attention for its emotional depth, dealing with themes of facing and overcoming personal demons and struggles.

Lower Than Atlantis is a British rock band from Watford, Hertfordshire, formed in 2007. They are known for their blend of rock, alternative rock, and punk influences, crafting a sound that resonated with a wide range of listeners. This catalog features songs from their entire discography which include the albums, Far Q, World Record, Changing Tune, Lower Than Atlantis and Safe In Sound. "Get Over It,” and “Here We Go” are both from their self-titled album, released in 2014. The album represented a pivotal moment for Lower Than Atlantis, showcasing a mix of hard-hitting rock anthems and melodic tunes that broadened their appeal.

Jonathan Thulin is a notable figure in the contemporary Christian music scene. His work is celebrated for its unique blend of pop and electronic music, infused with deep lyrical content that often explores themes of faith, hope, and redemption. Throughout his career, Thulin has received critical acclaim and several nominations for prestigious awards. Notably, he was nominated for three We Love Christian Music Awards, including Best Male Artist, Best Collaboration for "Dead Come to Life" (featuring Charmaine), and Best Music Video for "Bombs Away" (featuring Rachael Lampa). This listing includes all the songs from Jonathan Thulin's most notable albums: The Anatomy of a Heartflow (2012), The White Room (2013), and Science Fiction (2015).

"Jekyll and Hyde" was released in 2015 as part of Thulin's album Science Fiction. The song features New Zeeland Christian band, Rapture Ruckus and explores the internal struggle between conflicting parts of one's personality, much like the famous characters Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde. "Hat Trick,” featuring Derek Minor, is another standout track from Science Fiction. Thulin's evocative lyrics are complemented by Derek Minor's rap, which adds depth to the narrative by highlighting the pressures and consequences of maintaining a facade. "Architecture" was released in 2013 as part of the album The White Room. It is a powerful and introspective track that explores themes of love, support, and resilience.

'Dark Clouds' by Rod Wave, a standout track from his 2020 album 'Pray 4 Love,' has significantly impacted the hip-hop and rap scene. The song, known for its heartfelt lyrics and Rod Wave's soulful delivery, has resonated deeply with fans, becoming a social media favorite. The track charted on the Billboard Hot 100 and contributed to the album's peak at number 2 on the Billboard 200, achieving Certified Platinum by the RIAA. The song's success highlights the growing trend of melodic rap, blending singing and rapping, and has been prominently featured in music blogs, reviews, and social media, cementing Rod Wave's reputation as an impactful artist.

'Can't Take It (Ima Gangsta)' by Mozzy, a standout track from his 2017 album '1 Up Top AHK,' features a raw depiction of street life and gang culture. The song has garnered substantial streaming numbers and contributed to the album peaking at number 68 on the Billboard 200. 'Can't Take It (Ima Gangsta)' has been well-received by fans for its honesty and energy, featured in playlists, documentaries, and social media, cementing Mozzy's reputation as a compelling voice in hip-hop.

Simon Curtis is an American singer, songwriter, and actor who first gained attention in the Nickelodeon movie "Spectacular!" in 2009. Transitioning to music, he released his debut album "8Bit Heart" in 2010, followed by "RA" in 2011, "Super 8-Bit Heart" in 2016, and "Angel Aura" in 2023, all independently. His unique blend of electropop and dance-pop, characterized by video game sounds and themes, has earned him a dedicated following.

Curtis's albums have performed well in niche markets, amassing significant streaming numbers and positive critical reception. Collaborating with indie producers, Curtis has maintained creative control over his music. His music's presence in online media and fan communities further amplifies his digital footprint, solidifying his role as a significant independent artist in contemporary pop and electronic music.

Press Play is a dynamic Christian pop and rock band formed in 2008. Their music is a blend of pop, rock, and dance, featuring uplifting and faith-driven lyrics. This listing includes all the songs from the band’s four major albums: Life Is Beautiful (2009), NY2LA (2010), World Anthem (2011), and #LITO (2013). These albums were well-received, with Life Is Beautiful peaking at No. 2 on the Billboard Christian Albums chart and No. 45 on the Billboard 200 chart, showcasing their commercial success. NY2LA followed, reaching No. 3 on the Christian Albums chart.

“#LITO," which stands for "Love In The Open," is the title track of their album of the same name. The song has been featured in various media, including the 2014 film Project Almanac. "NY2LA," another of their standout tracks, combines energetic beats with a rap feature from Tyler James Williams, highlighting their knack for cross-genre collaborations.

Urban Rescue, an American Christian music group based in Los Angeles and active since 2009, specializes in a blend of worship, Christian pop, Christian EDM, and electropop. Their key commercial achievement is the 2016 studio album "Wild Heart," which topped the US & UK Christian Music charts.

Jesus Culture, founded in 1999, is a prominent Christian revivalist movement and worship band originating from Bethel Church in Redding, CA. Known for its passionate contemporary Christian music blending rock and pop elements, the group has released numerous influential albums and hosts global conferences, significantly impacting the modern worship movement.

Chris McClarney is a Christian worship leader and songwriter from Nashville, Tennessee, known for his soulful voice and impactful worship music. McClarney began his career leading worship in his local church and has since released several albums, including "Everything and Nothing Less," recorded live at the 2015 Jesus Culture Sacramento conference.
